  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Incidence of tourniquet-induced hypertension</measure>
    <time_frame>During the tourniquet inflation time period</time_frame>
    <description>Primary outcome is incidence of tourniquet-induced hypertension, which is defined as an increase of systolic or diastolic blood pressure &gt; 30% from baseline. This will be looked at during the time of tourniquet inflation (from inflation to deflation) during the actual surgical procedure. Usual maximum inflation time is 120 minutes.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
